SteveLOCKED IN 8/7/2024 7:12 PM
Starts with a cutscene of Yahiamice running in YER. Fades away like a simulation, where Yahi’s friend starts speaking about what happened. YAHIAMICE doesn’t remember anything, so his friend informs him about where he is: He is in a security complex which deals with the containment of this monster. He was in the simulation to determine the monster’s weaknesses. The monster is a demonic version of YAHIAMICE, where its mask is what is keeping it from destroying everything. His friend goes from the outside to the inside for the security, and features of the place. Ending on explaining the monster’s cell. the door lock is placed on the inside to make sure nobody lets it out, and the way to unlock it is by completing a math puzzle. Next you are given full free roam of the building for a while, until an alarm goes off. Coming back to the middle of the facility, the monster has solved the math puzzle and broken free. The other people working at the facility set it into lockdown, and leave you in the same room/area with the monster. There are 3 rooms. 1: isolation proximity The goal here is to unlock the large security door leading to the next area, and closer to leaving. Inside is very little. The only goal of this room is to lure the monster far enough away for the player to unlock the door with a password. The password is on the desk. The door won’t unlock with the monster nearby, so there are various ways to lure it away. TBD. Once that has been unlocked, the doors around the centre room open, revealing more puzzles to escape. 2: death encounters The goal here is to have the monster brute force a forcefield until it breaks. Throughout the room there are various traps that you can attack the monster with. These traps are mainly acid rain of sorts, slowly corroding the monster, but also making it able to slowly break the forcefield. There are 3 forcefields. Once each has been broken, there are levers behind them that need to be activated in a certain pattern. The pattern is somewhere in the room. Acid traps are also in the first room, but aren’t able to be used. There is a forcefield in the first room too. 3: security issues This room is pretty simple: FNAF of sorts with cats. Here you can fully disable the lockdown to escape, and there is no other way to leave. There is a thing that activates a countdown, which will slowly unlock every room. Each of these rooms holds a challenge that you will have to fight off. First is cats, which will immediately be attacking. They all require food, so you need to be sparing with it. They will all progressively get angrier before attacking. Feeding them will make hem fully calm for a bit. The next is boxes. They will appear at your door, and can sometimes contain cat food. Using a security camera, you can see if the box has anything on the top, or if it’s moving. If you open the door to a moving box, you are dead. Otherwise it’s cat food that is required for you to win. Other challenges will be gone during this part. Finally there’s the monster, which has the same mechanics from that one obby minigame. There is one window with 3 levers Instead some will be noise related. If tapping, shock. If you see movement in the dark, light it up. If that doesn’t deter it, close the door (will open after 3 seconds. It has delay. After surviving until 97%, there is a guaranteed time when the monster's legs will be cut off, meaning it will be crawling. That also means that it is inside, leading to a chase scene to the outside. Yahi cringes as he is about to be killed. Then nothing happens so he looks to see: one of those random objects to NCS music He checks the script, then looks to the object, and he shows it to the camera: Yahi fucking dies family guy pose The end lol (edited)
